    <item>
      <title>Development based on broadcast messages</title>
      <link>https://example.com/docs/landstar/1_%E5%9F%BA%E4%BA%8E%E5%B9%BF%E6%92%AD%E6%B6%88%E6%81%AF%E5%BC%80%E5%8F%91/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://example.com/docs/landstar/1_%E5%9F%BA%E4%BA%8E%E5%B9%BF%E6%92%AD%E6%B6%88%E6%81%AF%E5%BC%80%E5%8F%91/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Pre-preparation for receiving coordinates: Connect RTK satellite receiver, press power button to turn on satellite receiver, open LandStar software, confirm software is used under legal and registered premise, note that no project needs to be created or open existing project.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;connecting-rtk&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Connecting RTK&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#connecting-rtk&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The LandStar software connects to the data generation source through (Bluetooth/Wifi mode) or through a local connection. Switch to the configuration page, click the Connection menu or directly click the top to connect to the device navigation bar, and enter the Connected Instrument interface as shown below. Open the Bluetooth search target device, select it, and click the Connect button.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Quick Start</title>
      <link>https://example.com/docs/gnssserver/01_%E5%BF%AB%E9%80%9F%E5%BC%80%E5%A7%8B/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://example.com/docs/gnssserver/01_%E5%BF%AB%E9%80%9F%E5%BC%80%E5%A7%8B/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;quick-start&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Quick Start&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#quick-start&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;permissions&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Permissions&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#permissions&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Before using the SDK, make sure that the application has the necessary permissions. These permissions include Bluetooth (only Bluetooth connections are used in this section and WIFI is not involved), and the ability to read and write external storage, as the SDK requires external storage to read and write configuration files and log files. Please add permissions in &lt;code&gt;AndroidManifest.xml&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-xml&#34; data-lang=&#34;xml&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;!-- Permission to use Bluetooth features --&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;uses-permission&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;android:name=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;android.permission.BLUETOOTH&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;/&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;!-- Permission to administer Bluetooth settings --&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;uses-permission&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;android:name=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;android.permission.BLUETOOTH_ADMIN&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;/&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;!-- Permission to read from external storage --&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;uses-permission&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;android:name=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;/&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;!-- Permission to write to external storage --&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;uses-permission&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;android:name=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;/&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It should be noted that in Android10, Android11 and later versions, there will be some differences in the application method for external storage.&lt;/strong&gt; Android 10 introduces &#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;https://developer.android.com/about/versions/11/privacy/storage&#34;&gt;Scoped Storage&lt;/a&gt;, You can add the following code to AndroidManifest.xml:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Connection</title>
      <link>https://example.com/docs/gnssserver/02_%E8%BF%9E%E6%8E%A5/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://example.com/docs/gnssserver/02_%E8%BF%9E%E6%8E%A5/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;connection&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Connection&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#connection&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;connection-mode&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Connection Mode&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#connection-mode&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;bluetooth-connection&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Bluetooth connection&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#bluetooth-connection&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The main steps and codes for Bluetooth connection are as follows:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Configure the connection parameters via ReceiverConnectionOption;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Get the IReceiverConnectManager object from the service obtained in &#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;chapter1.md#sdk-initialization&#34;&gt;SDK Initialization&lt;/a&gt;;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Pass the ReceiverConnectionOption object obtained in &amp;ldquo;1&amp;rdquo; as a parameter to the connect method of IReceiverConnectManager object.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ol&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-java&#34; data-lang=&#34;java&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;// Connection event&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;mBTConnect.&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;setOnClickListener&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; View.&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;OnClickListener&lt;/span&gt;() {&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;@Override&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;void&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;onClick&lt;/span&gt;(View view) {&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;        &lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;// Connect directly through the SDK&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;        ReceiverConnectionOption option &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; ReceiverConnectionOption()&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;                .&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;setConnectionType&lt;/span&gt;(ConnectionType.&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;CONNECTION_BLUETOOTH&lt;/span&gt;)&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;                .&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;setProductName&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;SMART-RTK&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;)&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;                .&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;setBluetoothName&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#e6db74&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;GNSS-9999848&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;       &#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;        &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;            &lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;// Get receiverConnectManager through mService and then connect using receiverConnectManager&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;            IReceiverConnectManager receiverConnectManager &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; IReceiverConnectManager&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;                    .&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;Stub&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;asInterface&lt;/span&gt;(mService.&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;getReceiverConnectManager&lt;/span&gt;());&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;            &lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;// Connect using receiverConnectManager&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;            &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;!&lt;/span&gt;receiverConnectManager.&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;connect&lt;/span&gt;(option)) {&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;                &lt;span style=&#34;color:#75715e&#34;&gt;// Connection failure&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;            }&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;        } &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (RemoteException e) {&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;            &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;throw&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; RuntimeException(e);&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;        }&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    }&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;});&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;bluetooth-injection-connection-optional&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Bluetooth injection connection (optional)&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#bluetooth-injection-connection-optional&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Recommended use &amp;ldquo;Bluetooth connection&amp;rdquo; method in &amp;ldquo;Bluetooth Connection&amp;rdquo;, the connection method injected by Bluetooth here only provides a choice for developers with special needs.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Development based on txt file</title>
      <link>https://example.com/docs/landstar/2_%E5%9F%BA%E4%BA%8Etxt%E6%96%87%E4%BB%B6%E5%BC%80%E5%8F%91/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://example.com/docs/landstar/2_%E5%9F%BA%E4%BA%8Etxt%E6%96%87%E4%BB%B6%E5%BC%80%E5%8F%91/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Pre-preparation for receiving coordinates: Connect RTK satellite receiver, press power button to turn on satellite receiver, open LandStar software, confirm software is used under legal and registered premise, note that no project needs to be created or open existing project.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;connecting-rtk&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Connecting RTK&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#connecting-rtk&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The LandStar software connects to the data generation source through (Bluetooth/Wifi mode) or through a local connection. Switch to the configuration page, click the Connection menu or directly click the top to connect to the device navigation bar, and enter the Connected Instrument interface as shown below. Open the Bluetooth search target device, select it, and click the Connect button.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Receiver communication</title>
      <link>https://example.com/docs/gnssserver/03_%E6%8E%A5%E6%94%B6%E6%9C%BA%E9%80%9A%E4%BF%A1/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://example.com/docs/gnssserver/03_%E6%8E%A5%E6%94%B6%E6%9C%BA%E9%80%9A%E4%BF%A1/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;receiver-communication&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Receiver communication&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#receiver-communication&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;obtain-data-from-receiver&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Obtain data from receiver&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#obtain-data-from-receiver&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;After you get the service (refer to &#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;chapter1.md#sdk-initialization&#34;&gt;SDK Initialization&lt;/a&gt;), you can use the requestReceiverListener method of the service to monitor the receiver data. The requestReceiverListener requires you to pass in the IReceiverListener.Stub object. You can inherit the object, implement the relevant interface, and obtain the required data through the implementation of the interface. Some callback interfaces call back at a certain frequency (such as location information and satellite information), and some interfaces require a command to the receiver (refer to &#xA;  &lt;a href=&#34;https://example.com/#send-data-to-the-receiver-set-up-the-receiver&#34;&gt;Send data to the receiver&lt;/a&gt;) before calling back.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Coordinate conversion</title>
      <link>https://example.com/docs/gnssserver/04_%E5%9D%90%E6%A0%87%E8%BD%AC%E6%8D%A2/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://example.com/docs/gnssserver/04_%E5%9D%90%E6%A0%87%E8%BD%AC%E6%8D%A2/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;coordinate-conversion&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Coordinate conversion&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#coordinate-conversion&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This chapter introduces the setup functions related to coordinate system transformation, including setting source ellipsoid, target ellipsoid, projection parameters, datum conversion parameters and so on. Here we introduce the usage of related functions through the examples of forward and backward calculation, for more usage, readers can refer to the related interfaces given later.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;how-to-realize-forward-and-backward-calculation-by-sdk&#34;&gt;&#xA;  How to realize forward and backward calculation by SDK&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#how-to-realize-forward-and-backward-calculation-by-sdk&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;preparations&#34;&gt;&#xA;  Preparations&#xA;  &lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#preparations&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Whether it is a forward or backward calculation, the Coordinate Transformation needs to be initialized, and the parameters of the relevant conversion need to be set, the specific steps are as follows:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>IMU</title>
      <link>https://example.com/docs/gnssserver/05_imu/</link>
